The paper deals with zero-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses methods for visual-semantic embedding and domain adaptation, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions self-paced learning, which is a technique used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL and cs.MM.
